HEADWORD: Silicotungstic
<hw>Sil`i*co*tung"stic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, any one of a
series of double acids of silicon and tungsten, known in the free state,
and also in their salts (called <xex>silicotungstates</xex>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silicula</ent>⟦br⟧
